		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />On the Pasofami emulator's page, I saw something interesting.  But as I cannot speak Japanese I had to rely on Babelfish, which was almost unhelpful.  But I guess that they are making RAM carts for the most common memory mappers, 0-4 and using USB to connect to a PC.  The PC is using Pasofami to send the ROMs to the cart.  At least this is what I can make out.  
<br />
